# Testing Rules

## Unit Tests Required For
- Fee math
- Fair-probability calculations
- Order book state updates (determinism)
- Paper fill simulation (maker queue, taker depth, partial fills)
- Risk halt logic (every gate)
- Market lifecycle parsing
- Event serialization round-trip

## Integration Tests Required For
- Market discovery (Gamma/keyset endpoint)
- WebSocket subscription (CLOB market channel)
- Resolution-source feed ingestion
- Binance/Coinbase feed ingestion
- Geoblock check
- Storage write/read path

## Replay Tests
- Must be deterministic for identical input data and config.
- Verify no trades occur on stale reference data.
- Verify fee-adjusted P&L is stable.
- Verify market lifecycle transitions are correct.
- Determinism check must fail on intentional event drift.

## Failure Tests Required For
- Dropped Polymarket WebSocket
- Delayed Binance/Coinbase feed
- Missing/stale resolution-source feed
- Bad market metadata
- Book snapshot reset
- Rate-limit responses
- Geoblock-blocked response
- Storage outage

## Milestone Exit Gates
- Do NOT start next milestone until current exit gate passes.
- Exit gate = all build tasks complete + all verification checks pass + all done criteria met.
- Failing/skipped checks must be recorded with a reason before proceeding.
- M2+ requires API verification sections to be complete.
